The paper deals with strategic network formation games, which are typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The focus of the paper is on networks under attack, which falls under the category of network security (cs.NI). The paper also introduces a tractable model for network formation, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of social networks (cs.SI). The paper deals with the computational complexity of the game, which could be relevant to researchers in the field of cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for computing a minimal connection to a network, which is a problem in the field of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
